<ul>
    <li><strong>Sarah's Story:</strong> Texas BCBA with 52 students across 8 schools. Reduced crisis calls by 65% in 8 weeks. Now leaves by 5 PM most days—and her students are making better progress.</li>
    <li><strong>Marcus's Story:</strong> Sole BCBA in a rural district of 4,000 students. Built Tier 2 systems that empowered teachers. Now mentors two new BCBAs his district hired.</li>
    <li><strong>Jennifer's Story:</strong> 12-year veteran completely burned out. Tried everything—apps, self-care, therapy. What worked? Shifting from crisis manager to systems leader. Now she loves her job again.</li>
    <li><strong>The Pattern:</strong> When you stop being the system and start building systems, everything changes.</li>
</ul>
